channel.title: Runescape LookaLike
channel.description:
[CENTER][b]RuneScape MMPORG Server Base[/b] [i]Created by Canuowneasy[/i]
[b]100% made by Canuowneasy[/b] I take [i]no[/i] credit for this. I just posted it with you because it's a great starter base, I'm currently using it for my project.
[b]Overview:[/b]
[i][B]The Purpose[/B][/i]
I have created this for one and one only reason. To restart 317 private servers. I am trying to start a completely new base made from pure 317 runescape cache. This will offer no spelling/grammer mistakes. Everything on the base will be fully functional. No 'half-ass' work. The MMPORG is already very stable - even so, I plan to upgrade stability by adding an anti-flood system to the server.
[i][B]What's Your Base?[/B][/i]
Winterlove - not an edited version. The original flat out, no content release.
[i][B]Credits[/B][/i]
-Jagex LTD - Canuowneasy - Ben - Winterlove - Graham
[B]Features:[/B] - Stable - 7 skills done (Melee, Woodcutting, Mining, Fishing, Fletching, Magic, Prayer) - Correct attacking methods - NPC Dialogue - Almost perfect combat - Player Saving - Equiptment requirements - New stats interface - 100% Clan Chat - 100% Censors - Completely Anti-Flood. - Three Connections Per IP - Server Console - Trading - Private Message - Administrator + Moderator Crowns - New Interfaces - All NPC Drops - Player Design - ALL Hovering Stats - Thread Per Client
[B]Download:[/B] Pm me if Download it broken.
[B][COLOR=Red]Reply or link Deleted[/COLOR][/B]
[url=http://www.mediafire.com/download.php?mm1nodnmztn][b]Mediafire[/b][/url] [url=http://www.mediafire.com/download.php?mm1nodnmztn]http://www.mediafire.com/download.php?mm1nodnmztn[/url]
[b]Tutorials:[/b]
[b]Making Yourself Administrator:[/b]
[ul][*]Go into Config\Rights. [*]Add your name into administrators.[/ul]
[b]Editing Player Login:[/b] First, go to src\com\rs\worldserver\model\player and look for class Player.
[i]Changing Player XP on login[/i]
[ul][*]Do CTRL + F, search for playerXP[i] [*]Change the 14000000 to how much XP you want a player to start out with.[/ul]
[i]Changing Player levels on login[/i]
[ul][*]Do CTRL + F, search for playerLevel[i] [*]Change 99 to the level you want a player to start out with.[/ul]
[i]Changing Starter Gear[/i]
[ul][*]Do CTRL + F, search for playerEquipment [*]Change the item ids[/ul]
[i]Changing Default Entinity Clothing[/i]
[ul][*]Do CTRL + F, search for pHead [*]Change the numbers to what clothing id you want. (A number list is included above)[/ul]
